<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-08-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-08-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="98" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d98">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Denby</persName>, chargé.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-08-18"><hi rend="italic">August 18,
                                1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Chinese minister complains that the U. S. consul at Shanghai is
                            protecting Japanese spies. Report immediately and fully.</p>
                    </div>
